ons/access_loggers/wasm/`\n**Proto Definition**: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/wasm/v3/wasm.proto`\n**JSON Support**: DEPENDS - Determined by WASM plugin\n**Details**:\n- Generic wrapper using `WasmAccessLog` class\n- Delegates logging to dynamically loaded WASM module\n- Format determined by WASM plugin implementation\n- Supports access log filtering before WASM invocation\n- Format is configurable within the WASM module\n\n## Access Log Filter Implementations (Filtering Decisions)\n\nThese classes filter which requests should be logged (return true = log, false = skip):\n\n### Core Filters (in `source/common/access_log/`)\n\n1. **StatusCodeFilter** - Filters based on HTTP response status code using comparison operators\n2. **DurationFilter** - Filters based on total request/response duration in milliseconds\n3. **NotHealthCheckFilter** - Filters out health check requests\n4. **TraceableRequestFilter** - Logs only requests marked as traceable and service-forced\n5. **RuntimeFilter** - Filters based on runtime feature keys with percentage-based sampling\n6. **HeaderFilter** - Filters based on request header presence and values\n7. **ResponseFlagFilter** - Filters based on Envoy response flags (errors, timeouts, etc.)\n8. **GrpcStatusFilter** - Filters based on gRPC status codes (with HTTP status fallback)\n9. **LogTypeFilter** - Filters based on access log type (HTTP, TCP, etc.)\n10. **MetadataFilter** - Filters based on dynamic metadata presence or values\n11. **AndFilter** - Logical AND composition of sub-filters\n12. **OrFilter** - Logical OR composition of sub-filters\n\n### Extension Filters\n\n13. **CEL Filter** (in `source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/`)\n   - Evaluates Common Expression Language (CEL) expressions\n   - Location: `source/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/cel.h` (CELAccessLogExtensionFilter)\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/v3/cel.proto`\n   - Supports string conversion, concatenation, and manipulation functions\n   - Enables complex conditional logging based on request/response attributes\n\n## Proto Definitions Without C++ Implementations (v1.31.2)\n\nThe following proto definitions exist in data-plane-api but lack C++ implementations in this Envoy version:\n\n1. **Stats Access Logger**\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/stats/v3/stats.proto`\n   - Type: Access log sink that emits custom Envoy statistics\n   - Features: Configurable counters and histograms with tags and command operator values\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation in v1.31.2\n\n2. **Dynamic Modules Access Logger**\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto`\n   - Type: Access log sink for custom behavior via dlopen-loaded modules\n   - Features: Shared module loading, per-logger naming, flexible configuration via google.protobuf.Any\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation in v1.31.2\n\n3. **Process RateLimit Filter**\n   - Proto: `envoy/extensions/access_loggers/filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto`\n   - Type: Access log filter for global token bucket-based rate limiting\n   - Features: Dynamic token bucket configuration via ConfigSource\n   - Status: Proto defined but no C++ implementation in v1.31.2\n\n## JSON/Structured Logging Support Summary\n\n| Component | Type | JSON Support | Format |\n|-----------|------|--------------|--------|\n| File | Sink | YES | Text, JSON, Typed JSON |\n| Stdout/Stderr | Sink | YES | SubstitutionFormatString (text/JSON) |\n| gRPC HTTP | Sink | YES | Structured Protobuf (HTTPAccessLogEntry) |\n| gRPC TCP | Sink | YES | Structured Protobuf (TCPAccessLogEntry) |\n| Fluentd | Sink | YES | Structured MessagePack with JSON nesting |\n| OpenTelemetry | Sink | YES | Structured OTLP (KeyValueList, AnyValue) |\n| Wasm | Sink | DEPENDS | Plugin-defined |\n| CEL Filter | Filter | N/A | Expression-based selection |\n| Status Code | Filter | N/A | Comparison-based selection |\n| Duration | Filter | N/A | Numeric comparison-based selection |\n| Health Check | Filter | N/A | Boolean flag-based selection |\n\n## Key Architectural Notes\n\n1. **Base Class Hierarchy**: All sink implementations extend `Common::ImplBase` which handles filter evaluation before `emitLog()` call\n2. **Formatter Integration**: Most sinks use `Formatter::FormatterPtr` for flexible output formatting\n3. **Thread Safety**: Access loggers use thread-local storage via `ThreadLocal::SlotPtr` for efficient per-thread instances\n4. **Protobuf Messaging**: gRPC and OpenTelemetry loggers use structured protobuf messages for data transmission\n5. **Filter Extensibility**: `ExtensionFilterFactory` allows custom filter implementations (like CEL)\n6. **Configuration Factory Pattern**: Each access logger has a factory class implementing `AccessLogInstanceFactory`\n\n## Conclusion\n\nEnvoy v1.31.2 provides comprehensive access logging coverage with multiple sink implementations supporting both unstructured text logging and structured (JSON/protobuf) logging. The architecture is extensible via factory pattern and supports composition of filters through AND/OR operators. All major sink types (file, gRPC, Fluentd, OpenTelemetry, Wasm) support structured data in their respective formats."
